298
00:15:26.343 --> 00:15:28.529
Ooh. Chess.

299
00:15:28.553 --> 00:15:30.239
I love smart people.

300
00:15:30.263 --> 00:15:32.098
So you hate yourself.

301
00:15:33.141 --> 00:15:35.077
♪ Get out of my way ♪

302
00:15:35.101 --> 00:15:37.955
♪ or I might shove ♪

303
00:15:37.979 --> 00:15:39.915
♪ Get out of my way ♪

304
00:15:39.939 --> 00:15:42.627
♪ or I'm gonna shove ♪

305
00:15:42.651 --> 00:15:44.295
It's a total straw man argument.

306
00:15:44.319 --> 00:15:46.839
No one actually thinks that Eddie Vedder

307
00:15:46.863 --> 00:15:50.009
-is better than Kurt Cobain.
-Thank you.

308
00:15:50.033 --> 00:15:51.761
Now if you were to say Chris Cornell...

309
00:15:51.785 --> 00:15:53.953
No way. dude.

310
00:16:09.386 --> 00:16:11.429
Did you do anything fun over the summer?

311
00:16:12.847 --> 00:16:13.932
Mm-hmm.

312
00:16:15.016 --> 00:16:16.035
What?

313
00:16:16.059 --> 00:16:18.371
This summer. Did you do anything fun?

314
00:16:18.395 --> 00:16:19.479
What do you mean?

315
00:16:24.567 --> 00:16:26.045
W-What's that?

316
00:16:26.069 --> 00:16:27.421
A zine.

317
00:16:27.445 --> 00:16:29.924
Oh. like. a magazine?

318
00:16:29.948 --> 00:16:34.804
I have two subscriptions to Cosmo.
one for my archives and one I can crease.

319
00:16:34.828 --> 00:16:36.871
No. like. a zine.

320
00:16:38.415 --> 00:16:41.310
Cool. What else are you into?

321
00:16:41.334 --> 00:16:43.187
Did-did someone put you up to this?

322
00:16:43.211 --> 00:16:46.691
I'm Elle. I like iced coffee.
the month of July.

323
00:16:46.715 --> 00:16:50.510
and when people dress kind of tennisy.
even if they don't play tennis.

324
00:16:51.594 --> 00:16:52.637
Was it Kimberly?

325
00:16:54.514 --> 00:16:56.909
Uh. welcome to first period.

326
00:16:56.933 --> 00:16:58.994
I am Mr. Nichols.

327
00:16:59.018 --> 00:17:01.604
and this is...

328
00:17:02.689 --> 00:17:04.917
English. Okay.

329
00:17:04.941 --> 00:17:07.753
Let's just dive right into it.

330
00:17:07.777 --> 00:17:12.174
Much Ado About Nothing.

331
00:17:12.198 --> 00:17:14.468
It was the shortest thing
on your summer reading list.

332
00:17:14.492 --> 00:17:17.871
so it's kind of a gimme. Ah. yes?

333
00:17:18.955 --> 00:17:20.850
First of all. nice to meet you.

334
00:17:20.874 --> 00:17:24.729
Second of all.
I never received a summer reading list.

335
00:17:24.753 --> 00:17:26.814
It was mailed out in May.

336
00:17:26.838 --> 00:17:29.859
Yeah. I. uh...
I actually didn't know

337
00:17:29.883 --> 00:17:31.360
I'd be going to this school
until kind of recently.

338
00:17:31.384 --> 00:17:34.613
There was this whole thing with my dad.

339
00:17:34.637 --> 00:17:36.449
Don't ask.

340
00:17:36.473 --> 00:17:38.909
Like. seriously don't ask.
I can't talk about it.

341
00:17:38.933 --> 00:17:40.643
NDA.

342
00:17:41.811 --> 00:17:43.456
Well. you'll have
to read the play this week.

343
00:17:43.480 --> 00:17:47.084
because you will each be writing a paper
on its themes

344
00:17:47.108 --> 00:17:48.836
this weekend.

345
00:17:48.860 --> 00:17:53.215
Hi. At my old school.
we were given the option

346
00:17:53.239 --> 00:17:55.009
to have our own take on the assignment.

347
00:17:55.033 --> 00:17:56.343
Is that an option here?

348
00:17:56.367 --> 00:17:57.928
Uh. your own take?

349
00:17:57.952 --> 00:18:01.807
Yeah. Like. we could create a song
based on the reading or a short film.

350
00:18:01.831 --> 00:18:04.268
I went to middle school
with Tim Burton's nephew.

351
00:18:04.292 --> 00:18:06.145
and you have not experienced
Tuck Everlasting

352
00:18:06.169 --> 00:18:08.171
until you've seen it in stop-motion.

353
00:18:09.964 --> 00:18:12.651
I'm sure I haven't. but I would say "no."

354
00:18:12.675 --> 00:18:15.029
That's not an option.

355
00:18:15.053 --> 00:18:16.679
A paper is a paper.

356
00:18:18.264 --> 00:18:19.390
Oh.

357
00:18:22.018 --> 00:18:24.771
Just try to keep up. Okay?

358
00:18:26.022 --> 00:18:28.292
So. Much Ado About Nothing.
What is it? It is a play.

359
00:18:28.316 --> 00:18:30.085
And what do we know about it?

360
00:18:30.109 --> 00:18:34.340
It was written by William Shakespeare.
the great bard himself.

361
00:18:34.364 --> 00:18:37.760
We're still accepting donations
for the auction.

362
00:18:37.784 --> 00:18:40.036
Still accepting donations for the auction.

363
00:18:41.037 --> 00:18:42.473
We're still accepting donations
for the auction.

364
00:18:42.497 --> 00:18:44.725
Holy Pierce Brosnan.

365
00:18:44.749 --> 00:18:47.520
-We're accepting donations.
-A kindred spirit.

366
00:18:47.544 --> 00:18:51.339
So nice to meet a fellow stranger
in a strange land.

367
00:18:52.423 --> 00:18:53.925
Did I see you this morning?

368
00:18:55.009 --> 00:18:58.697
You're the guy who almost hit
my mom's car with your skateboard.

369
00:18:58.721 --> 00:19:00.825
I thought you were a jerk.
but you're just British.

370
00:19:00.849 --> 00:19:03.494
You're used to driving
on the wrong side of the road.

371
00:19:03.518 --> 00:19:05.621
which I totally get.

372
00:19:05.645 --> 00:19:08.040
Not the driving thing.
I'm not from here. either.

373
00:19:08.064 --> 00:19:09.500
Wow.

374
00:19:09.524 --> 00:19:11.460
Is this place different. right?

375
00:19:11.484 --> 00:19:12.628
Right.

376
00:19:12.652 --> 00:19:14.922
Have you noticed
how many hoodies they wear?

377
00:19:14.946 --> 00:19:17.091
What is that about?

378
00:19:17.115 --> 00:19:18.884
I'm Elle Woo... Oh.

379
00:19:18.908 --> 00:19:22.930
Dustin. And I've lived here
for. like. nine years.

380
00:19:22.954 --> 00:19:25.391
so that's most of my life.

381
00:19:25.415 --> 00:19:26.892
Cool.

382
00:19:26.916 --> 00:19:29.252
I'll just go to my locker.

383
00:19:34.799 --> 00:19:37.135
Which is right by yours. Great.

384
00:19:41.347 --> 00:19:42.533
Oh.

385
00:19:42.557 --> 00:19:45.327
Uh. you can't really open both
at the same time.

386
00:19:45.351 --> 00:19:48.438
Okay. I'll just go after you. then.

387
00:20:01.659 --> 00:20:04.203
Look. I just need
to get my lunch money from here.

388
00:20:10.293 --> 00:20:11.502
Okay.

389
00:20:15.214 --> 00:20:16.215
What even are those?

390
00:20:17.634 --> 00:20:19.385
I don't know if it's really your thing.

391
00:20:23.723 --> 00:20:26.035
What's happening with the support staff?

392
00:20:26.059 --> 00:20:27.518
Not getting paid a living wage.

393
00:20:29.687 --> 00:20:31.731
It's been all over the news.

394
00:20:33.358 --> 00:20:37.004
Okay.
The news is a nonfictional TV show

395
00:20:37.028 --> 00:20:40.716
that connects real people to real issues.

396
00:20:40.740 --> 00:20:43.618
-Hmm?
-I know what the news is.

397
00:20:44.702 --> 00:20:46.496
Great. She's all yours.

398
00:20:54.128 --> 00:20:56.190
Thank you.

399
00:20:56.214 --> 00:20:57.757
Mmm.

400
00:21:01.177 --> 00:21:02.446
-Hi. Could you help me with something?
-Come on. man.

401
00:21:02.470 --> 00:21:04.782
Sorry. I'm just trying
to get the lay of the land.

402
00:21:04.806 --> 00:21:07.451
Like. what cliques are where.
who sits with who.

403
00:21:07.475 --> 00:21:09.954
Yeah. I still feel like
you're messing with me.

404
00:21:09.978 --> 00:21:12.289
What's the. uh. agenda here?

405
00:21:12.313 --> 00:21:14.291
I'm not messing with you.

406
00:21:14.315 --> 00:21:16.961
I just have this whole three-point plan.
and the first step is to let...

407
00:21:16.985 --> 00:21:19.129
Band geeks.

408
00:21:19.153 --> 00:21:21.298
Jocks.

409
00:21:21.322 --> 00:21:24.009
D&D nerds.

410
00:21:24.033 --> 00:21:25.493
Stoners.

411
00:21:26.786 --> 00:21:28.514
Kids of parents with Microsoft money.

412
00:21:28.538 --> 00:21:31.124
And kids of parents with Boeing money.

413
00:21:40.591 --> 00:21:42.194
Hi. again.

414
00:21:42.218 --> 00:21:43.511
Which ones are the stoners?

415
00:21:46.472 --> 00:21:47.825
-Crazy.
-No way.

416
00:21:47.849 --> 00:21:49.308
And the Microsoft kids?

417
00:21:51.602 --> 00:21:52.788
Seriously?

418
00:21:52.812 --> 00:21:55.457
Hmm.

419
00:21:55.481 --> 00:21:57.626
Could you just point me
in the direction of the senior girls?

420
00:21:57.650 --> 00:21:59.420
And if one of them could have won.

421
00:21:59.444 --> 00:22:02.589
Homecoming Queen or one
of the top-tier superlatives. even better.

422
00:22:02.613 --> 00:22:06.301
Oh. okay. So. you're not looking
for just any old person.

423
00:22:06.325 --> 00:22:09.638
You want a cool senior
who can totally boost your popularity?

424
00:22:09.662 --> 00:22:11.789
Yes. exactly.

425
00:22:12.957 --> 00:22:15.102
You should be friends
with that girl over there.

426
00:22:15.126 --> 00:22:17.187
The one with the curly hair.

427
00:22:17.211 --> 00:22:20.298
-Do you want to come with. or...?
-Oh. no. I'm good.

428
00:22:28.890 --> 00:22:30.284
Hi. ladies.

429
00:22:30.308 --> 00:22:33.412
I was told this is where
the coolest of the cool seniors sit.

430
00:22:33.436 --> 00:22:37.273
Well. technically. I'm a junior.
but. spiritually. I'm a senior.

431
00:22:38.691 --> 00:22:39.668
Oh.

432
00:22:39.692 --> 00:22:41.277
You're... sitting.

433
00:22:43.488 --> 00:22:45.841
Wait. I thought we were going
to the Bikini Kill show that weekend.

434
00:22:45.865 --> 00:22:47.158
So fun.

435
00:22:48.242 --> 00:22:49.845
You know Bikini Kill?

436
00:22:49.869 --> 00:22:51.805
Oh.

437
00:22:51.829 --> 00:22:53.849
I know bikinis.

438
00:22:53.873 --> 00:22:55.416
That kill.

439
00:23:00.213 --> 00:23:03.275
Okay. Whose car are we taking? Or are we
seriously taking a bus to Olympia?

440
00:23:03.299 --> 00:23:04.610
What about Miles's?

441
00:23:04.634 --> 00:23:06.195
We can't take a guy's car
to a Bikini Kill show.

442
00:23:06.219 --> 00:23:07.446
I mean. think of how that would look.

443
00:23:07.470 --> 00:23:10.991
Oh. I totally feel your struggle.
All of my friends at home have cars.

444
00:23:11.015 --> 00:23:13.327
It's impossible not to have one
if you live in L.A.

445
00:23:13.351 --> 00:23:17.122
But instead of getting me a car.
my parents moved me to Seattle. Hmm.

446
00:23:17.146 --> 00:23:19.708
L.A.

447
00:23:19.732 --> 00:23:20.918
Yeah. that explains it.

448
00:23:20.942 --> 00:23:22.652
You must be so happy to have escaped.

449
00:23:24.237 --> 00:23:25.923
What's wrong with L.A.?

450
00:23:25.947 --> 00:23:28.967
Nothing. I-I think
we just value different things here.

451
00:23:28.991 --> 00:23:32.286
like the planet and social justice.

452
00:23:33.371 --> 00:23:37.184
And not being totally entitled and sitting
wherever we want in the cafeteria

453
00:23:37.208 --> 00:23:42.004
on our first day when some of us
have spent four years earning this table.

454
00:23:46.884 --> 00:23:49.053
Have you ever actually been to L.A.?

455
00:23:51.806 --> 00:23:56.829
Uh. no. No. you couldn't pay any of us
to set foot in California.

456
00:23:56.853 --> 00:24:00.541
And this little exchange
is not changing my mind.

457
00:24:00.565 --> 00:24:03.794
Okay. before L.A. Barbie
interrupted us. the jackets.

458
00:24:03.818 --> 00:24:05.003
-Right. the jackets.
-Yeah.

459
00:24:05.027 --> 00:24:07.321
You know the ones?

460
00:24:17.373 --> 00:24:19.017
Okay. Yeah.

461
00:24:19.041 --> 00:24:22.020
Okay. I'll have him get back to you.

462
00:24:22.044 --> 00:24:23.564
All right. sweetie. Well. good to hear

463
00:24:23.588 --> 00:24:25.357
-she's doing well. Bye.
-Hi.

464
00:24:25.381 --> 00:24:26.966
Hi.

465
00:24:27.550 --> 00:24:29.468
Love the bobbleheads. Très chic.

466
00:24:32.138 --> 00:24:36.451
Could I see the school nurse?
I'm not. um...

467
00:24:36.475 --> 00:24:38.287
-feeling well.
-Hang on a second. Caleb.

468
00:24:38.311 --> 00:24:40.164
Cafeteria's that way.

469
00:24:40.188 --> 00:24:42.124
Yeah.
I think I'm just gonna skip it today.

470
00:24:42.148 --> 00:24:44.209
Not gonna happen.

471
00:24:44.233 --> 00:24:45.568
Come here.

472
00:24:49.030 --> 00:24:51.115
-I'm serious.
-Thank you. Donna.

473
00:24:55.036 --> 00:24:56.621
Why is he skipping lunch?

474
00:24:58.456 --> 00:24:59.892
His parents haven't paid for school lunch.

475
00:24:59.916 --> 00:25:03.312
but the boy's got to eat.
and I have petty cash. so...

476
00:25:03.336 --> 00:25:05.272
That's so nice.

477
00:25:05.296 --> 00:25:07.298
No one at my old school
would've done that.

478
00:25:08.382 --> 00:25:13.113
Well. the way I see it is that
it is my job to look out for all of you.

479
00:25:13.137 --> 00:25:15.365
And if that means

480
00:25:15.389 --> 00:25:19.578
sneaking into the cafeteria to get someone
a piece of cake for their birthday.

481
00:25:19.602 --> 00:25:24.458
or signing a permission slip
that their parents forgot to sign.

482
00:25:24.482 --> 00:25:27.526
you know.
some rules are made to be broken.

483
00:25:30.863 --> 00:25:32.490
Is that a Cosmo?

484
00:25:33.574 --> 00:25:34.843
You can tell by the corner?

485
00:25:34.867 --> 00:25:36.202
Of course.

486
00:25:37.161 --> 00:25:41.350
All right.
I know this may not seem like my thing.

487
00:25:41.374 --> 00:25:43.977
but. oh. those little quizzes
are so addictive.

488
00:25:44.001 --> 00:25:45.312
I know!

489
00:25:45.336 --> 00:25:49.358
And their horoscopes have been right
on several occasions.

490
00:25:49.382 --> 00:25:51.401
-It's kind of my bible.
-Oh. my God. Me. too.

491
00:25:51.425 --> 00:25:54.321
I-I just moved here. so I'm waiting for
my subscription to get forwarded here.

492
00:25:54.345 --> 00:25:55.489
Mm.

493
00:25:55.513 --> 00:25:56.555
Could I just...?

494
00:25:59.809 --> 00:26:01.811
Thank you.

495
00:26:08.484 --> 00:26:09.860
Hmm.

496
00:26:10.945 --> 00:26:14.383
Hi. Donna. Um. just give me five.

497
00:26:14.407 --> 00:26:17.511
and then I'm gonna make a few phone calls.

498
00:26:17.535 --> 00:26:18.971
Yeah. Absolutely.

499
00:26:18.995 --> 00:26:21.789
Now. there is just one more form
I need you to fill out.

500
00:26:24.166 --> 00:26:27.562
We kind of have a "no chitchat" policy
here in the office.

501
00:26:27.586 --> 00:26:29.130
I totally understand.

502
00:26:29.964 --> 00:26:32.401
Now. I could call your parents

503
00:26:32.425 --> 00:26:35.678
and tell them you have a 24-hour bug
or something.

504
00:26:36.512 --> 00:26:38.365
Or you could spend your lunch in here.

505
00:26:38.389 --> 00:26:40.367
doing that very important paperwork.
of course.

506
00:26:40.391 --> 00:26:43.311
-Mm-hmm.
-And you could give this place a chance.

507
00:26:44.687 --> 00:26:46.206
What kind of chance?

508
00:26:46.230 --> 00:26:49.293
Well. if this was your first day
at your old school.

509
00:26:49.317 --> 00:26:51.193
how would you be spending it?

510
00:26:54.572 --> 00:26:55.716
Hmm.

511
00:26:55.740 --> 00:26:59.136
L-E-T-S-G-O.
that's the way we spell "Let's go."

512
00:26:59.160 --> 00:27:01.972
Let's go. Hey. hey. let's go.

513
00:27:01.996 --> 00:27:05.750
And I don't know your mascot.
so go. team. go.

514
00:27:10.629 --> 00:27:12.065
Thank you.

515
00:27:12.089 --> 00:27:14.067
I mean. wack.

516
00:27:14.091 --> 00:27:15.277
It's fine. You're in.

517
00:27:15.301 --> 00:27:18.155
Oh. Really?

518
00:27:18.179 --> 00:27:21.682
Don't you need to take a few days
and put up a list or something?

519
00:27:22.475 --> 00:27:24.310
Nah. you're in.

520
00:27:25.394 --> 00:27:27.456
Great. Thank you so much. ladies.

521
00:27:27.480 --> 00:27:28.999
I won't let you down.

522
00:27:29.023 --> 00:27:30.316
Next.

523
00:27:36.238 --> 00:27:37.573
Good luck.

524
00:27:41.410 --> 00:27:45.265
L-E-T-S-G-O.
that's the way we spell "Let's go."

525
00:27:45.289 --> 00:27:48.143
Let's go. Hey. hey. let's go.

526
00:27:48.167 --> 00:27:49.353
Great. you're in.

527
00:27:49.377 --> 00:27:50.878
Sweet.

528
00:27:56.092 --> 00:27:57.736
Oh!

529
00:27:57.760 --> 00:27:59.446
-Oh.
-Oh.

530
00:27:59.470 --> 00:28:01.865
-Sorry.
-It's okay. Whew.

531
00:28:01.889 --> 00:28:03.349
Are you okay?

532
00:28:04.934 --> 00:28:08.080
Yeah. I'm great.

533
00:28:08.104 --> 00:28:10.106
-So great.
-Okay.

534
00:28:10.773 --> 00:28:12.191
Okay.

535
00:28:21.075 --> 00:28:22.618
Are you sure you're all right?

536
00:28:24.453 --> 00:28:26.056
Does this school not have a football team?

537
00:28:26.080 --> 00:28:30.143
If so. I can't imagine
they're very highly motivated since...

538
00:28:30.167 --> 00:28:32.270
Yeah. football's not really a thing here.

539
00:28:32.294 --> 00:28:33.838
So who do they root for?

540
00:28:34.463 --> 00:28:38.467
I think girls here think
cheering for boys is lame.

541
00:28:40.344 --> 00:28:44.515
So they just... cheer for themselves?

542
00:28:47.935 --> 00:28:49.353
You got a name?

543
00:28:50.438 --> 00:28:51.480
Elle Woods.

544
00:28:52.440 --> 00:28:53.708
Elle... Woods.

545
00:28:53.732 --> 00:28:54.859
Yeah.

546
00:29:04.535 --> 00:29:05.679
-Okay.
-Ooh.

547
00:29:05.703 --> 00:29:06.805
Mm-hmm.

548
00:29:06.829 --> 00:29:10.058
I have to say. I love my office.

549
00:29:10.082 --> 00:29:11.768
Aw.

550
00:29:11.792 --> 00:29:14.896
-I knew you would.
-Yeah. and the nice thing about

551
00:29:14.920 --> 00:29:18.650
the slower pace is that I-I feel like
I can really spend time with my patients.

552
00:29:18.674 --> 00:29:20.402
like I might actually make a difference.

553
00:29:20.426 --> 00:29:21.528
Me. too.

554
00:29:21.552 --> 00:29:23.447
-Yeah?
-Can you believe

555
00:29:23.471 --> 00:29:25.949
they didn't have Tae Bo here yet?

556
00:29:25.973 --> 00:29:28.309
-Such an interesting place. Eva.
-Yes.

557
00:29:28.976 --> 00:29:30.245
What about you?

558
00:29:30.269 --> 00:29:32.247
-How's the new school?
-Yeah. you said

559
00:29:32.271 --> 00:29:33.772
you tried out for cheer. How was it?

560
00:29:35.149 --> 00:29:37.127
I don't think I'm gonna join.

561
00:29:37.151 --> 00:29:40.571
The girls here just kind of cheer
for themselves.

562
00:29:41.655 --> 00:29:43.199
-I don't get it.
-Hmm.

563
00:29:44.283 --> 00:29:45.927
I think it's feminism.

564
00:29:45.951 --> 00:29:48.597
Yeah. that's very in right now.

565
00:29:48.621 --> 00:29:49.848
Hmm.

566
00:29:49.872 --> 00:29:52.350
It's probably
why Marlena came back to life.

567
00:29:52.374 --> 00:29:54.936
Can you believe
she's not even possessed anymore?

568
00:29:54.960 --> 00:29:56.128
She did?

569
00:29:58.214 --> 00:30:01.109
Honey. Oh. no.
I-I left the tape in your room.

570
00:30:01.133 --> 00:30:02.402
I thought you'd watched it already.

571
00:30:02.426 --> 00:30:04.470
Well. I was saving it
for a pre-dinner treat.

572
00:30:08.974 --> 00:30:10.952
I can't believe we moved here.

573
00:30:10.976 --> 00:30:14.915
This will do you
no more good than your bothersome prayers

574
00:30:14.939 --> 00:30:19.085
and your irksome holy water.

575
00:30:19.109 --> 00:30:22.297
Oh. all right. all right. all right!

576
00:30:22.321 --> 00:30:24.799
I'll play your game.

577
00:30:24.823 --> 00:30:26.927
I've been playing right along.

578
00:30:26.951 --> 00:30:29.387
It's not even worth it.

579
00:30:29.411 --> 00:30:32.289
What should be my next move?

580
00:30:37.878 --> 00:30:40.172
Marlena's possession was all I had.

581
00:30:48.347 --> 00:30:49.390
Hmm.

582
00:30:53.519 --> 00:30:55.747
Elle Woods' residence.
You've reached Elle Woods.

583
00:30:55.771 --> 00:30:57.958
Elle!

584
00:30:57.982 --> 00:30:59.626
Madison?

585
00:30:59.650 --> 00:31:01.419
Elle. I just got a car phone.

586
00:31:01.443 --> 00:31:02.796
What?

587
00:31:02.820 --> 00:31:05.549
Madison? I can't hear you.

588
00:31:05.573 --> 00:31:07.968
I got a car phone!

589
00:31:07.992 --> 00:31:10.011
Oh! That's so cool.

590
00:31:10.035 --> 00:31:11.596
I know. right?

591
00:31:11.620 --> 00:31:13.932
-Tiffany and Amber are here. too.
-Hi. Elle.

592
00:31:13.956 --> 00:31:15.642
We don't have time for hellos.
Sorry. Elle.

593
00:31:15.666 --> 00:31:17.143
I only have two minutes on this thing

594
00:31:17.167 --> 00:31:19.646
before I start getting charged a gazillion
dollars and my parents kill me.

595
00:31:19.670 --> 00:31:21.314
But the headline is...

596
00:31:21.338 --> 00:31:23.716
-school was crazy today.
-So crazy.

597
00:31:25.092 --> 00:31:26.528
That-that sounds really fun. you guys.

598
00:31:26.552 --> 00:31:27.779
It was.

599
00:31:27.803 --> 00:31:29.781
-Jeff got a really unfortunate earring.
-Oh.

600
00:31:29.805 --> 00:31:31.032
And Susie got even more

601
00:31:31.056 --> 00:31:33.827
unfortunate highlights. and I think that
Chad and Becca are a thing even though

602
00:31:33.851 --> 00:31:35.078
they're still pretending like they're not.

603
00:31:35.102 --> 00:31:36.830
No. it was literally. like.
a hall of fame first day.

604
00:31:36.854 --> 00:31:39.124
That's exactly
what I was going to say.

605
00:31:39.148 --> 00:31:40.584
-Hall of fame. Yeah.
-Right?

606
00:31:40.608 --> 00:31:44.004
Wow.

607
00:31:44.028 --> 00:31:48.133
Um... has Hot Josh asked

608
00:31:48.157 --> 00:31:49.408
about me?

609
00:31:50.534 --> 00:31:53.096
Not so much in his words.
but in his actions.

610
00:31:53.120 --> 00:31:55.098
-absolutely.
-Mm-hmm.

611
00:31:55.122 --> 00:31:57.183
But enough about us.
How was your first day?

612
00:31:57.207 --> 00:31:59.102
Did you make any friends?

613
00:31:59.126 --> 00:32:00.794
Does the school secretary count?

614
00:32:01.879 --> 00:32:04.590
-That's a great jumping-off point.
-Mm-hmm.

615
00:32:05.299 --> 00:32:06.568
I just...

616
00:32:06.592 --> 00:32:09.863
I don't feel like I really speak
the same language as anyone here.

617
00:32:09.887 --> 00:32:11.698
Well. have you tried
learning their language?

618
00:32:11.722 --> 00:32:12.949
What do you mean?

619
00:32:12.973 --> 00:32:14.826
-Get fluent in Seattle.
-Mm.

620
00:32:14.850 --> 00:32:17.329
I don't know if that's possible.

621
00:32:17.353 --> 00:32:19.289
Oh. I'm sorry. Elle. Two minutes are up.

622
00:32:19.313 --> 00:32:20.707
-We-we miss you.
-We love you!

623
00:32:20.731 --> 00:32:22.232
Well. I miss you guys.

624
00:32:24.693 --> 00:32:25.986
Bye.

625
00:32:31.533 --> 00:32:33.994
Get fluent in Seattle.

626
00:32:39.458 --> 00:32:42.086
♪ Live. baby. live ♪

627
00:32:42.878 --> 00:32:45.005
♪ now that the day is over ♪

628
00:32:47.257 --> 00:32:50.678
♪ I got a new sensation ♪

629
00:32:52.054 --> 00:32:55.700
♪ In perfect moments ♪

630
00:32:55.724 --> 00:32:59.728
♪ that's impossible to refuse ♪

631
00:33:02.731 --> 00:33:05.293
♪ Sleep. baby. sleep ♪

632
00:33:05.317 --> 00:33:07.403
♪ now that the night is over ♪

633
00:33:10.698 --> 00:33:13.009
♪ And the sun comes like a god ♪

634
00:33:13.033 --> 00:33:14.928
Hey.

635
00:33:14.952 --> 00:33:17.079
-♪ Into our room ♪
-Hey. girl.

636
00:33:18.831 --> 00:33:23.419
♪ All perfect light and promises ♪

637
00:33:26.004 --> 00:33:27.482
♪ got a hold on you ♪

638
00:33:27.506 --> 00:33:30.527
♪ A new sensation ♪

639
00:33:30.551 --> 00:33:31.903
Elle. right?

640
00:33:31.927 --> 00:33:33.387
Yes. Elle Woods.

641
00:33:34.138 --> 00:33:36.533
-And you are Kimberly.
-Mm.

642
00:33:36.557 --> 00:33:38.201
From yesterday.

643
00:33:38.225 --> 00:33:40.620
There's a rumor going around that
I feel like I should make you aware of.

644
00:33:40.644 --> 00:33:42.288
Out of love.

645
00:33:42.312 --> 00:33:43.915
Oh. my God. what is it?

646
00:33:43.939 --> 00:33:47.961
Well. people are saying that you wearing
that shirt is the second worst thing

647
00:33:47.985 --> 00:33:50.588
to ever happen to Nirvana.

648
00:33:50.612 --> 00:33:54.074
Wait. I'm sorry. Did you replace the eyes
with little hearts?

649
00:33:54.825 --> 00:33:57.244
I leaned into its innate smiley-ness.

650
00:33:58.495 --> 00:34:00.615
Did no one ever tell you
that we don't do posers here?

651
00:34:02.040 --> 00:34:03.393
Seattle isn't a costume.

652
00:34:03.417 --> 00:34:06.044
and pink isn't a personality.

653
00:34:52.591 --> 00:34:54.259
Mom?

654
00:34:55.719 --> 00:34:57.095
Bruiser?

655
00:34:58.096 --> 00:34:59.807
Anyone?

656
00:35:15.614 --> 00:35:18.426
Hi! You've reached Madison LeDoux's car.

657
00:35:18.450 --> 00:35:20.094
I've run out of minutes for this month.

658
00:35:20.118 --> 00:35:22.621
but leave a message
and I'll listen to it in 27 days.

659
00:35:55.946 --> 00:35:57.382
Mom?

660
00:35:57.406 --> 00:35:59.157
In here.

661
00:36:06.665 --> 00:36:08.393
What is this?

662
00:36:08.417 --> 00:36:12.296
No one could be expected to succeed
in that much gray.

663
00:36:17.342 --> 00:36:18.594
Wait.

664
00:36:27.060 --> 00:36:28.538
You hate it?

665
00:36:28.562 --> 00:36:30.081
-No.
-W... I got

666
00:36:30.105 --> 00:36:32.065
the wrong shade?
You wanted Spring Watermelon?

667
00:36:34.818 --> 00:36:36.570
What?

668
00:36:37.321 --> 00:36:38.739
I love it.

669
00:36:39.698 --> 00:36:41.301
Does your face know you love it?

670
00:36:41.325 --> 00:36:43.052
I do. That's the problem.

671
00:36:43.076 --> 00:36:44.971
I'm-I'm shallow.

672
00:36:44.995 --> 00:36:48.725
What kind of person has
the worst day of her life solved by...

673
00:36:48.749 --> 00:36:50.417
pink drapery?

674
00:36:51.251 --> 00:36:52.628
A nice one.

675
00:36:53.712 --> 00:36:57.525
What if I really am the vapid L.A. girl
they all think I am?

676
00:36:57.549 --> 00:36:59.444
Well. I don't know
if you should be putting so much stock

677
00:36:59.468 --> 00:37:01.613
in the opinions of people
who wear leather jewelry.

678
00:37:01.637 --> 00:37:02.780
You don't understand.

679
00:37:02.804 --> 00:37:04.866
They fight for things like social justice

680
00:37:04.890 --> 00:37:07.243
and hold student auctions

681
00:37:07.267 --> 00:37:09.728
and they write their own... zines.

682
00:37:11.980 --> 00:37:13.124
What's a zine?

683
00:37:13.148 --> 00:37:14.650
Exactly.

684
00:37:16.568 --> 00:37:17.819
You know who you are?

685
00:37:18.820 --> 00:37:20.739
You're a Gemini.

686
00:37:21.782 --> 00:37:23.843
I bet they hate astrology. too.

687
00:37:23.867 --> 00:37:26.930
That means you are funny

688
00:37:26.954 --> 00:37:29.432
and smart and adaptable.

689
00:37:29.456 --> 00:37:31.893
And you find a way
to make all types of friends.

690
00:37:31.917 --> 00:37:34.228
You say they have depth? They care?

691
00:37:34.252 --> 00:37:36.254
Well. so do you.

692
00:37:38.173 --> 00:37:39.508
You're right.

693
00:37:40.634 --> 00:37:42.177
I do care.

694
00:37:43.470 --> 00:37:45.347
You just have to show them that.

695
00:37:53.647 --> 00:37:55.375
-Oh. hi. Donna.
-Hey.

696
00:37:55.399 --> 00:37:58.461
-Have you seen Dustin?
-Uh. yeah. he's right over there.

697
00:37:58.485 --> 00:38:01.130
I want to see
if he needs help with his auction.

698
00:38:01.154 --> 00:38:02.548
Does this mean you've made a friend?

699
00:38:02.572 --> 00:38:04.133
Way to fit in.

700
00:38:04.157 --> 00:38:05.551
-Sort of.
-All right.

701
00:38:05.575 --> 00:38:07.015
-Go get 'em. tiger.
-Thanks. Donna.

702
00:38:08.245 --> 00:38:09.639
Okay then.

703
00:38:09.663 --> 00:38:12.392
If. uh. pasta's not your thing.

704
00:38:12.416 --> 00:38:14.143
Yeah. but what about...

705
00:38:14.167 --> 00:38:15.627
this basketball?

706
00:38:16.628 --> 00:38:19.107
Is there anything special
about this basketball? It's...

707
00:38:19.131 --> 00:38:20.316
Oh. okay. it's just a basketball.

708
00:38:20.340 --> 00:38:22.443
It's just a basketball. but it...

709
00:38:22.467 --> 00:38:24.553
it's a nice basketball.

710
00:38:26.138 --> 00:38:27.347
This is embarrassing.

711
00:38:28.682 --> 00:38:30.910
I guess I will just keep it for myself.

712
00:38:30.934 --> 00:38:32.662
-All right. what's next?
-Uh.

713
00:38:32.686 --> 00:38:33.955
a-a vase from my mom.

714
00:38:33.979 --> 00:38:37.125
A... vase from Jake's mum.

715
00:38:37.149 --> 00:38:38.567
Any starting bids?

716
00:38:39.317 --> 00:38:41.236
Nah.

717
00:38:42.029 --> 00:38:44.424
I have something I'd like to say.

718
00:38:44.448 --> 00:38:48.243
-This should be good.
-This isn't just any vase.

719
00:38:49.870 --> 00:38:51.889
It is a...

720
00:38:51.913 --> 00:38:54.559
multiuse art piece.

721
00:38:54.583 --> 00:38:56.894
It can hold flowers.

722
00:38:56.918 --> 00:39:00.189
It can serve as an organizer
for your school supplies.

723
00:39:00.213 --> 00:39:03.133
Or it can just look nice.

724
00:39:04.426 --> 00:39:05.778
What are you doing?

725
00:39:05.802 --> 00:39:08.281
I am helping the support staff
of this school.

726
00:39:08.305 --> 00:39:10.616
who are being vastly underpaid.

727
00:39:10.640 --> 00:39:12.100
Don't you watch the news?

728
00:39:12.684 --> 00:39:13.995
The first rule of fundraising is

729
00:39:14.019 --> 00:39:15.288
you have to be a salesperson.

730
00:39:15.312 --> 00:39:16.372
Watch.

731
00:39:16.396 --> 00:39:20.251
This vase is also an investment piece.

732
00:39:20.275 --> 00:39:22.128
-Let's say Justin's mom...
-Jacob.

733
00:39:22.152 --> 00:39:26.007
Jacob's mom blows up as an artist
in the next few years.

734
00:39:26.031 --> 00:39:28.634
Do you know how much money
you could make off of this?

735
00:39:28.658 --> 00:39:31.679
Potentially thousands of dollars.

736
00:39:31.703 --> 00:39:33.347
Mm-hmm. mm-hmm.

737
00:39:33.371 --> 00:39:34.915
Twenty bucks.

738
00:39:40.087 --> 00:39:42.190
We have 20 bucks. That's a steal.

739
00:39:42.214 --> 00:39:43.465
Twenty-five.

740
00:39:45.342 --> 00:39:47.111
Ooh! Not bad!

741
00:39:47.135 --> 00:39:48.946
But can anyone beat that?

742
00:39:48.970 --> 00:39:50.430
Thirty.

743
00:39:53.975 --> 00:39:55.369
Going once.

744
00:39:55.393 --> 00:39:56.871
going twice.

745
00:39:56.895 --> 00:39:58.581
Sold to...

746
00:39:58.605 --> 00:39:59.898
Miles.

747
00:40:00.732 --> 00:40:02.317
-Miles.
-Yeah!

748
00:40:05.821 --> 00:40:06.988
I got it.

749
00:40:12.327 --> 00:40:13.304
Okay. what's next?

750
00:40:13.328 --> 00:40:14.514
-Here you go.
-Oh.

751
00:40:14.538 --> 00:40:15.598
It's. uh...

752
00:40:15.622 --> 00:40:16.849
it's really something.

753
00:40:16.873 --> 00:40:17.999
I have to come clean.

754
00:40:18.583 --> 00:40:20.770
Jacob's mom's never going
to make it in the art world.

755
00:40:20.794 --> 00:40:22.563
I am so sorry.

756
00:40:22.587 --> 00:40:24.524
Well. you could've convinced me.

757
00:40:24.548 --> 00:40:26.818
Actually. you did convince me.
That's why I bought it.

758
00:40:26.842 --> 00:40:28.945
Are we doing this?

759
00:40:28.969 --> 00:40:30.238
Yes.

760
00:40:30.262 --> 00:40:31.489
Thanks again.

761
00:40:31.513 --> 00:40:32.597
What's next?

762
00:40:35.392 --> 00:40:37.453
Ooh. a jersey.

763
00:40:37.477 --> 00:40:41.940
A Ken Griffey Jr. jersey.

764
00:40:43.817 --> 00:40:45.652
Let's start the bidding at 20.

765
00:40:48.697 --> 00:40:50.115
How about 15?

766
00:40:54.703 --> 00:40:56.121
Okay. look.

767
00:40:56.621 --> 00:40:58.623
Who cares about Ken Griffey Jr.?

768
00:41:00.125 --> 00:41:04.588
What-what I mean is. we all
obviously care about Ken Griffey Jr.

769
00:41:05.964 --> 00:41:09.402
But who we care about more
are the people who care about us.

770
00:41:09.426 --> 00:41:11.636
The support staff of the school.

771
00:41:12.429 --> 00:41:13.889
Like Donna.

772
00:41:15.348 --> 00:41:18.161
Donna's let me eat lunch in her office
every day since I've been here.

773
00:41:18.185 --> 00:41:19.704
even when she wasn't supposed to.

774
00:41:19.728 --> 00:41:21.581
You guys.

775
00:41:21.605 --> 00:41:24.441
she pays for some students' lunches
using petty cash.

776
00:41:25.775 --> 00:41:26.878
Alison.

777
00:41:26.902 --> 00:41:29.172
she's turned a blind eye to your tardies.

778
00:41:29.196 --> 00:41:31.615
She knows it's not your fault
when your mom's been late.

779
00:41:32.824 --> 00:41:35.803
And that's not even mentioning
the permission slips she's signed.

780
00:41:35.827 --> 00:41:37.597
the unexcused absences she doesn't mark.

781
00:41:37.621 --> 00:41:39.724
And I've only been at this school
a couple days.

782
00:41:39.748 --> 00:41:42.602
This is money
going directly into Donna's pocket.

783
00:41:42.626 --> 00:41:46.254
And into the pocket of dozens
of other Donnas at this school.

784
00:41:47.047 --> 00:41:48.608
So I'll ask you again.

785
00:41:48.632 --> 00:41:53.112
Who wants this Ken Griffey Jr. jersey?

786
00:41:53.136 --> 00:41:54.071
Twenty bucks.

787
00:41:54.095 --> 00:41:55.489
Yay!

788
00:41:55.513 --> 00:41:56.598
Thirty.

789
00:41:59.059 --> 00:42:00.244
Thirty-five!

790
00:42:00.268 --> 00:42:01.394
Okay. Alison!

791
00:42:02.562 --> 00:42:04.248
-Not bad.
-Yeah. well. looks like

792
00:42:04.272 --> 00:42:05.875
I'm not as shallow as you thought.

793
00:42:05.899 --> 00:42:07.484
I never said you were shallow.

794
00:42:08.568 --> 00:42:09.736
Out loud.

795
00:42:10.570 --> 00:42:11.571
Going once.

796
00:42:13.031 --> 00:42:14.699
Going twice.

797
00:42:16.076 --> 00:42:18.036
Sold to Alison!

798
00:42:23.124 --> 00:42:25.895
Donna. Donna. Donna.

799
00:42:25.919 --> 00:42:31.609
Donna! Donna! Donna! Donna!

800
00:42:31.633 --> 00:42:34.362
Donna! Donna! Donna!

801
00:42:34.386 --> 00:42:38.783
Donna! Donna! Donna!

802
00:42:38.807 --> 00:42:40.576
Donna! Donna!

803
00:42:40.600 --> 00:42:42.686
Donna!

804
00:42:50.193 --> 00:42:51.754
Oh. Donna!

805
00:42:51.778 --> 00:42:53.113
-Take care. girls.
-Bye. Donna.

806
00:43:02.289 --> 00:43:03.683
Hey. 90210.

807
00:43:03.707 --> 00:43:05.226
Get anyone fired lately?

808
00:43:05.250 --> 00:43:06.811
What?

809
00:43:06.835 --> 00:43:08.271
Oh. you didn't hear?

810
00:43:08.295 --> 00:43:10.672
Your little stunt yesterday
got Donna fired.

811
00:43:12.215 --> 00:43:13.276
Turns out. when you announce

812
00:43:13.300 --> 00:43:16.696
every single rule someone's broken
to the entire school.

813
00:43:16.720 --> 00:43:18.656
they get punished for it.

814
00:43:18.680 --> 00:43:19.740
Who knew?

815
00:43:19.764 --> 00:43:22.285
Oh. well. maybe except everyone.

816
00:43:22.309 --> 00:43:23.703
That's n...

817
00:43:23.727 --> 00:43:25.788
I was just trying to help.

818
00:43:25.812 --> 00:43:26.872
Oh. yeah?

819
00:43:26.896 --> 00:43:28.273
How'd that go?

820
00:43:32.152 --> 00:43:34.654
♪ But I'm a creep ♪

821
00:43:37.615 --> 00:43:41.161
♪ I'm a weirdo ♪

822
00:43:42.162 --> 00:43:45.582
♪ What the hell am I doing here? ♪

823
00:43:48.418 --> 00:43:50.670
Okay. I can do this.

824
00:43:52.672 --> 00:43:54.233
Everything just feels backwards here.

825
00:43:54.257 --> 00:43:55.901
This doesn't seem sanitary.

826
00:43:55.925 --> 00:43:57.320
Happy Monday. Pink Slip.

827
00:43:57.344 --> 00:43:58.738
Oh. this isn't a slip.

828
00:43:58.762 --> 00:44:01.365
It's more of an alpaca tweed.

829
00:44:01.389 --> 00:44:02.366
I assume you're mad at me. too.

830
00:44:02.390 --> 00:44:03.993
I actually didn't even notice you.

831
00:44:04.017 --> 00:44:05.560
Which. I don't know. is that worse?

832
00:44:06.895 --> 00:44:08.539
High school is hard for everyone.

833
00:44:08.563 --> 00:44:09.749
no matter where you live.

834
00:44:09.773 --> 00:44:11.834
Kimberly's obviously relishing

835
00:44:11.858 --> 00:44:12.793
my fall from grace.

836
00:44:12.817 --> 00:44:16.213
I think you're overestimating
how much people liked you before this.

837
00:44:16.237 --> 00:44:18.299
But you are going to win over

838
00:44:18.323 --> 00:44:20.909
this entire city before you know it.

839
00:44:24.162 --> 00:44:25.348
-You could be concussed.
-I'm fine.

840
00:44:25.372 --> 00:44:28.092
On the drive over here. you claimed
your favorite color was charcoal.

841
00:44:28.541 --> 00:44:29.518
I did not say that.

842
00:44:29.542 --> 00:44:31.729
Just testing your short-term memory.
You passed.

843
00:44:31.753 --> 00:44:33.439
I kind of like someone here

844
00:44:33.463 --> 00:44:35.316
who I really can't like.

845
00:44:35.340 --> 00:44:36.758
Is it unrequited?

846
00:44:37.926 --> 00:44:39.320
How could it be unrequited?
You're Elle Woods.

847
00:44:39.344 --> 00:44:41.096
I'm sorry I said that.

848
00:44:42.889 --> 00:44:44.241
I don't know
why you won't give that girl

849
00:44:44.265 --> 00:44:45.493
a chance.

850
00:44:45.517 --> 00:44:47.286
And maybe there are
other sides to me.

851
00:44:47.310 --> 00:44:48.621
Maybe I'm not the rule-abiding.

852
00:44:48.645 --> 00:44:49.872
Gemini I always thought.

853
00:44:49.896 --> 00:44:52.315
When did detention get so uncool?

854
00:44:53.483 --> 00:44:54.418
I have this petition.

855
00:44:54.442 --> 00:44:55.860
It's for the greater good.

856
00:44:56.361 --> 00:44:57.463
Why won't you fight this with me?

857
00:44:57.487 --> 00:44:59.632
Because neither of us have a law degree.

858
00:44:59.656 --> 00:45:01.467
I have a Jackie O suit skirt

859
00:45:01.491 --> 00:45:02.760
I have been dying to mobilize.

860
00:45:02.784 --> 00:45:03.886
God. I miss L.A.

861
00:45:03.910 --> 00:45:05.638
At least there we could keep Elle safe

862
00:45:05.662 --> 00:45:07.014
from the criminal element.

863
00:45:07.038 --> 00:45:08.998
She trick-or-treated
at the Menendez house.

864
00:45:10.041 --> 00:45:11.685
I feel like
I don't even know you.

865
00:45:11.709 --> 00:45:13.962
When you're ready to be Elle Woods again.
give me a call.

866
00:45:15.380 --> 00:45:17.483
I think you got to ask yourself
who you'd rather disappoint.

867
00:45:17.507 --> 00:45:19.318
your mom or yourself.

868
00:45:19.342 --> 00:45:20.694
Officer. can we arrest her?

869
00:45:20.718 --> 00:45:22.196
Absolutely not.

870
00:45:22.220 --> 00:45:23.280
She's in Chanel.

871
00:45:23.304 --> 00:45:25.783
E-L-L-E!

872
00:45:25.807 --> 00:45:27.892
That's how we spell "victory"!

873
00:45:28.601 --> 00:45:29.853
Yes.

874
00:45:35.024 --> 00:45:36.484
♪ But I'm a creep ♪

875
00:45:40.530 --> 00:45:44.492
♪ I'm a weirdo ♪

876
00:45:45.535 --> 00:45:49.247
♪ What the hell am I doing here? ♪

877
00:45:51.040 --> 00:45:54.002
♪ I don't belong here ♪

878
00:45:54.836 --> 00:45:56.939
♪ Oh. oh ♪

879
00:45:56.963 --> 00:46:01.944
♪ She's running out ♪

880
00:46:01.968 --> 00:46:06.014
♪ the door ♪

881
00:46:08.057 --> 00:46:12.955
♪ She's running out ♪

882
00:46:12.979 --> 00:46:16.959
♪ She run. run. run ♪

883
00:46:16.983 --> 00:46:23.990
♪ run... ♪
